<section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <p class="faq-sub">Common questions textile owners ask before choosing a software partner.</p>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How long does textile ERP implementation take?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">A focused module like knitwear job-work or processing lot management goes live in 12 to 16 weeks. A full multi-stage textile ERP covering spinning, weaving, processing, garmenting and export documentation typically runs 5 to 7 months including data migration, shop-floor UAT and training in Tamil and English.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can the ERP track yarn lot through to finished garment?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. We carry a yarn lot identifier from cotton bale receipt through ring-frame doff, cone winding, warp/weft, dye lot, knit roll, cut bundle and finished garment carton. Every stage stamps the parent lot so you can trace a finished export carton back to the original cotton supplier and shade dye-bath — useful for buyer audits and BIS/Oeko-Tex documentation.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you support Tirupur job-work flow with in/out challan?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Tirupur knitwear runs on third-party fabricators for knitting, dyeing, embroidery, printing and finishing. We build delivery challan (out), receipt challan (in), with quantity reconciliation, shrinkage allowance, rate cards per process and GST job-work invoicing under section 143. ITC-04 returns are auto-prepared for upload.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Does your ERP integrate with auto-cutters, CAD and CAM?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. We export cut order plans to Lectra, Gerber and Optitex marker files, and import production data back from auto-cutters and sewing-line PLCs. For embroidery we exchange DST and EMB files with Tajima, Barudan and ZSK machines. Third-party product names are trademarks of their respective owners.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How do you handle multi-shift spinning mill data?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Our spinning module captures spindle-level production per shift A, B and C, with count change tracking, doff weight, hank conversion, soft waste and hard waste at ring frame, simplex and carding. Daily efficiency is computed per machine and per shift supervisor, with a TPM/OEE-style dashboard for the mill manager.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Is GST e-invoicing for export with LUT supported?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. We generate IRN through GSP/IRP, e-invoice QR code, e-way bill, shipping bill data, packing list, certificate of origin and LUT-based zero-rated export invoices. Multi-GSTIN setups across Tamil Nadu, Karnataka and Gujarat are supported out of the box, with consolidated GSTR-1 and GSTR-3B preparation.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you support Tamil-language interface for shop floor?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Shop-floor screens for spinning, weaving, processing and sewing-line entry render in Tamil with an English toggle. Operators see machine names, count, shade and bundle data in Tamil while management reports run in English. We also support Hindi and Gujarati for north and west India clusters such as Bhilwara, Ludhiana and Surat.</div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

